## Background and Motivation

I'm trying to implement a filter to unify the API result, for the `OkObjectResult`/`BadRequestResult`/... I can pattern match with `ObjectResult`, while there's no `ObjectHttpResult` to do something similar, so I'm proposing to add `ObjectHttpResult` and `OkObjectHttpResult`/... inherits `ObjectHttpResult`

## Proposed API

```diff
namespace Microsoft.AspNetCore.Http;

+public abstract class ObjectHttpResult: IResult
+{
+    protected ObjectHttpResult(){}
+    protected ObjectHttpResult(int statusCode) => StatusCode = statusCode;
+    public object? Value { get; }
+    public int StatusCode { get; }
+    public virtual Task ExecuteAsync(HttpContext httpContext);
+}

-public sealed class OkObjectHttpResult : IResult
+public sealed class OkObjectHttpResult : ObjectHttpResult(200)
{
}
```

## Usage Examples

``` c#
if (context.Result is ObjectHttpResult objectResult)
{
    var result = new Result<object>()
    {
        Data = objectResult.Value,
        Status = HttpStatusCode2ResultStatus(objectResult.StatusCode)
    };
    objectResult.Value = result;
}
```

## Risks

Not sure if it would introduce some breaking changes

